A health worker prepares the reports of COVID-19 tests. AFP/Johan Ordonez JOHANNESBURG - Almost 1,600 new COVID-19 cases have been recorded, taking the total number of cases to over 1,5 million. Sadly, 75 more people died, pushing the death toll to 53,498. READ: COVID-19 vaccine: 10 million Pfizer doses expected The recovery rate is at 95 percent with just over 21,000 active cases. The Johnson & Johnson vaccine trial is still on hold, but the country is expected to begin receiving the Pfizer jabs in May. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 561 559 the total number of deaths is 53 498 the total number of recoveries is 1 486 873. pic.twitter.com/OQjZoz2ASA